---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="The career arc from environmental scientist to AI consultant, via government, startups, and Valencia.">
  <section>
    <div class="container--narrow about-intro">
      <img src="/icon-512.png" alt="Matt Upson" class="headshot" />
      <div>
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p class="lead mt-3">I&rsquo;ve spent the last decade building AI systems and leading teams in government, not-for-profits, and startups. I co-founded Mantis NLP, an AI consultancy, and served as CEO and then CTO over five years. I now work independently with organisations who need senior AI capability without the overhead of a full-time hire.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="alt">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h2>The career arc</h2>
      <ol class="timeline">
        <li>
          <span class="timeline-role">Research Fellow &amp; PhD Researcher <span class="timeline-dates">2011&ndash;2015</span></span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Cranfield University, modelling forest growth and soil carbon storage</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="timeline-role">Data Scientist <span class="timeline-dates">2015&ndash;2016</span></span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Department for Education (first data scientist recruited to the department)</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="timeline-role">Data Scientist <span class="timeline-dates">2016&ndash;2018</span></span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Government Digital Service (GDS), pioneered Reproducible Analytical Pipelines</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="timeline-role">Lead Data Scientist <span class="timeline-dates">2018&ndash;2019</span></span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Juro, AI-enabled contract management platform</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="timeline-role">Founder &amp; CEO, then CTO <span class="timeline-dates">2021&ndash;2025</span></span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Mantis NLP, built to profitability over 5 years</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="timeline-role">Consultant (Network Member) <span class="timeline-dates">2019&ndash;present</span></span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Public Digital, digital transformation for governments</span>
        </li>
        <li class="timeline-now">
          <span class="timeline-role">Independent AI Consultant</span>
          <span class="timeline-org">Based in Valencia, Spain</span>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h2>The human stuff</h2>
      <p>I live in Valencia, Spain with my family. When I&rsquo;m not working, I&rsquo;m usually training for a triathlon, running along the Turia, or trying to improve my Spanish. My career path was unusual: I started as an environmental scientist, retrained in data science, and found my way to AI via government. That non-linear route means I bring a different perspective to most AI consultants; I understand research rigour, public interest constraints, and the gap between academic AI and production systems.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="alt">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h2>Speaking</h2>
      <p>I speak at conferences about AI leadership, responsible AI, and what actually works when deploying AI in government and mission-driven organisations.</p>
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EZXDfnel4Fw" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="card-link">
        <div class="card mt-3">
          <h3>Debugging Leadership: Six Errors when Moving From Code to Management</h3>
          <p class="text-muted">PyData London 2025</p>
          <p>Lessons from the transition from Data Scientist to Co-Founder, framed as Python errors. From battling imposter syndrome (<code>ValueError</code>) to learning to delegate (<code>DeadlockError</code>) and avoiding burnout (<code>RuntimeError</code>).</p>
          <span class="read-more">Watch on YouTube &rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h2>More</h2>
      <div class="more-links">
        <a href="/archive" class="card-link">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Blog archive</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">Everything I&rsquo;ve written since 2014, across Medium, Substack, government blogs, and machinegurning.blog.</p>
            <span class="read-more">View archive &rarr;</span>
          </div>
        </a>
        <a href="/papers" class="card-link">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Academic papers</h3>
            <p class="text-muted">Publications in data science, agroforestry, and soil carbon from my previous life as an environmental scientist.</p>
            <span class="read-more">View papers &rarr;</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-intro {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .headshot {
    width: 160px;
    height: 160px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .about-intro {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .timeline {
    list-style: none;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .timeline li {
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: -2.35rem;
    top: 0.35rem;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .timeline-now::before {
    background: var(--color-accent) !important;
  }

  .timeline-role {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .timeline-org {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .timeline-dates {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .more-links {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .more-links {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .card-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }

  .read-more {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>
